    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/figure-table-interpretation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The algorithm is available as part of the open-source software package OpenMS and runs on all major operating systems... The presented algorithm is implemented as part of the OpenMS framework. OpenMS, together with TOPP (The OpenMS Proteomics Pipeline), was designed as a versatile and functional framework for developing mass spectrometry data analysis tools, providing rich functionality ranging from basic data structures to sophisticated algorithms for data analysis and visualization.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms OpenMS, TOPP tools, TOPPView, and label-free quantification workflows. However, the paper does not mention SILAC, iTRAQ, TMT, SRM, or SWATH quantification methods\u2014only label-free quantification is discussed. The claim overstates the scope of quantification methods demonstrated in this paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1074-mcp-m113-031278",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "figure-table-interpretation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
